args: Look at the size of this pumpkin!\nPretty impressive, if I do say so myself.
Why are you covered in dirt like a common\npeasant, Your Highness?
Well, yes. I can see that much.
I was more asking why His Royal Highness\nis mucking about in dirt in the first place.
I'm helping to prepare for the party.
Apparently we're still short on decorations,\nso I went pumpkin hunting.
That's useful context, yet still fails to\nexplain why you—our leader, and royalty\nto boot—are performing manual labor.
You are lord of this castle. Leave tasks of\nthat nature to those of us who serve you.
Well, I suppose that's the way it would\nnormally work.
I am glad we're in agreement.
But that's not how I want to do things.
I'm helping out because I WANT to.\nI'm excited to be a part of everything.
*sigh* I should have expected as much.
Then at least allow me to help you.\nI trust you have no problem with that?
That would be great. Thanks, Elly.
...All right. I think that should be enough.
Thanks, Elly. That went much faster with\ntwo of us.
Heh. I'm actually a bit tired out.\nThese things are heavy!
Why don't you rest there for a spell?\nI'll bring you something to drink.
I think I'll rest for a spell as well.\nDo you mind if I sit beside you?
I knew you were unusual for a prince,\nbut I'd not expected you to take an\ninterest in tilling the soil.
Oh? I think there's a certain appeal\nto working the land.
But when I said this was nice, I was\ntalking about helping organize the party.
Back in the capital, they used to hold\ngrand festivals in the city below, but I\nalways had to watch from the castle.
I always wanted to actually take part in\none instead of just...seeing it.
Halloween seemed especially fun, but that\nwas off-limits for a whole host of reasons.
Ah. That's why you were so eager to help.
Yep. Heck, I jumped at the chance.
I mean, attending a party that you\nactually helped put together?
I'm sure it's a trivial thing to most people,\nbut to me, it's a dream long in the making.
Oh, I knew all that physical labor was a\nbad idea! Stay with me, Your Highness!\nDon't go toward the light!
He's...sleeping? Oh, phew! I nearly had\nheart failure for a moment there.
Still, the hard ground is no suitable pillow\nfor a prince.
My lap is mostly muscle, but it should still\nbe softer than the land.
Though now that I think on it, this is a\nrather intimate position. We must look to\nall the world like a pair of love...
N-no! It's not what it... I mean, this isn't...\nWe are certainly NOT!
Gah! The more I try to explain it,\nthe worse it sounds!
Please, Ranzal, it isn't what you think!\nYou have to believe me... PLEASE!
